Parliament, Sunday, 21June 2020 – National Assembly Deputy Speaker, Mr Lechesa Tsenoli, and National Council of Provinces Deputy Chairperson, Ms Sylvia Lucas, will today host a virtual Father’s Day men’s dialogue themed: “Fathers Speak to Heal the Nation.”
	
	This national men’s dialogue – to be held in partnership with the Department of Social Development and the South African National Aids Council Men’s Sector - aims to discuss the role of men towards a healthy nation; facilitating an environment that is conducive and safe for children to grow and thrive; and being allies and partners towards women’s well-being.
	
	Details of the virtual dialogue:
	
	Date: Sunday, 21 June 2020
	Time: 12:00
	
	Members of the media who would like to be part of the dialogue to observe may forward their contact details to Mr Mlindi Mpindi on email : mmpindi@parliament.gov.za for inclusion in the Parliament Communications Service WhatsApp group, where login details will be shared. Journalists are urged to forward these requests using their official email addresses (no private email)
	
	For media interviews with the NA Deputy Speaker, Mr Lechesa Tsenoli and NCOP Deputy Chairperson, Ms Sylvia Lucas, contact Mr Mlindi Mpindi on 081 716 7329.
	
	Members of the public may get involved and follow the dialogue live on Parliament TV (DStv Channel 408), via live stream on Parliament YouTube channel and Twitter page on the links below. You may subscribe to the Parliament YouTube channel to receive instant notification of live feeds.
	
	Twitter: https://twitter.com/ParliamentofRSA
	Facebook: https://facebook.com/ParliamentofRSA
	YouTube: https://www.youtube.com/ParliamentofRSA
	
